{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775816187976,"sessionID":"ses_2891d7ce7ffeWrz5twmBqnJUqZ","part":{"id":"prt_d76e2a5ce001JeIc7e3dKDAc3W","messageID":"msg_d76e291c4001ge9Xtbi2AU9JHk","sessionID":"ses_2891d7ce7ffeWrz5twmBqnJUqZ","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_54000b125eef46b18a55a65a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand:\n\n1. Find the pkg/workloadmanager directory structure and existing files\n2. Look for any existing design documents (design.md files) in the project\n3. Find any existing sandbox-related code or CRD definitions\n4. Check for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter type definitions in pkg/apis/runtime/\n5. Look for any existing workload manager interfaces or patterns\n6. Check if there's a sandbox controller or processor already\n7. Find any existing test patterns in the project\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- The directory structure of pkg/workloadmanager (if exists)\n- Key types and interfaces found\n- Existing patterns for controllers/processors\n- Any relevant CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter spec structures)\n- Testing patterns used in the project","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2891d4b55ffeHdm59YKOImpRhq (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Summary: AgentCube Project Exploration\n\n### 1. Directory Structure of `pkg/workloadmanager`\n\n**The `pkg/workloadmanager` directory does NOT exist on disk.** This benchmark project contains **specification documents** (reverse-engineered from the upstream GitHub repository `github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube`), not actual Go source code. The specs describe what the code *should* look like.\n\nAccording to the design documents, the expected structure is:\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n  server.go          - Server struct, Config, HTTP routes, Start()\n  handlers.go        - handleHealth, handleAgentRuntimeCreate, handleCodeInterpreterCreate, handleDeleteSandbox\n  workload_builder.go - buildSandboxObject, buildSandboxClaimObject, createSandbox, deleteSandbox\n  informers.go       - AgentRuntimeGVR, CodeInterpreterGVR, SandboxGVR, SandboxClaimGVR, informer sync\n  sandbox_controller.go - SandboxReconciler, WatchSandboxOnce, getSandboxStatus\n  garbage_collector.go - garbageCollector struct, gcLoop (15s interval)\n  auth.go            - authMiddleware, validateServiceAccountToken, context keys\n  k8s_client.go      - K8sClient, ClientCache, GetOrCreateUserK8sClient\n  defaults.go        - DefaultSandboxTTL (8h), DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout (15m), label/annotation keys\n```\n\n### 2. Design Documents Found\n\nTen design.md files exist in `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/`:\n\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Sandbox Orchestration | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/design.md` |\n| Code Execution (PicoD) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/code-execution/design.md` |\n| Deployment | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md` |\n| Session Store | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-store/design.md` |\n| Idle Cleanup (agentd) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/idle-cleanup/design.md` |\n| Session Routing (Router) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-routing/design.md` |\n| Python SDK | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/design.md` |\n| CLI Toolkit | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/design.md` |\n| CI/CD | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/ci-cd/design.md` |\n| Integrations (Dify) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/integrations/design.md` |\n\nPlus corresponding `spec.md` files for each domain, a `project.md`, and `test_spec.md`.\n\n### 3. Sandbox-Related Code/CRD Definitions\n\nFrom the specs, the following sandbox-related resources are defined:\n\n**External CRDs (from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`):**\n- **Sandbox** (`agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`) - The actual sandbox pod abstraction\n- **SandboxClaim** (`extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`) - For warm pool pre-allocation\n- **SandboxTemplate** (`extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`) - Template reference\n- **SandboxWarmPool** (`extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`) - Warm pool management\n\n**AgentCube-native CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`):**\n- **AgentRuntime** - Full pod template-based sandbox orchestration\n- **CodeInterpreter** - Simplified code execution sandbox with warm pool support\n\n**GVR Variables:**\n```\nAgentRuntimeGVR    = runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/agentruntimes\nCodeInterpreterGVR = runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/codeinterpreters\nSandboxGVR         = agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes\nSandboxClaimGVR    = extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxclaims\n```\n\n### 4. AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Type Definitions\n\n**AgentRuntime** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go`):\n```go\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort         `json:\"targetPort\"`\n    Template           *SandboxTemplate     `json:\"podTemplate\"`        // Required\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration     `json:\"sessionTimeout\"`     // Default \"15m\"\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration     `json:\"maxSessionDuration\"` // Default \"8h\"\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    Labels      map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n    Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n    Spec        corev1.PodSpec    `json:\"spec\"`  // Required - full PodSpec\n}\n```\n\n**CodeInterpreter** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`):\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort                    `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n    Template           *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate `json:\"template\"`         // Required\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration                `json:\"sessionTimeout\"`   // Default \"15m\"\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration                `json:\"maxSessionDuration\"` // Default \"8h\"\n    WarmPoolSize       *int32                          `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n    AuthMode           AuthModeType                    `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"` // Default \"picod\", enum: picod|none\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n    Ready      bool               `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {\n    Labels           map[string]string               `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n    Annotations      map[string]string               `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n    RuntimeClassName *string                         `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n    Image            string                          `json:\"image,omitempty\"`\n    ImagePullPolicy  corev1.PullPolicy               `json:\"imagePullPolicy,omitempty\"`\n    ImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference   `json:\"imagePullSecrets,omitempty\"`\n    Environment      []corev1.EnvVar                 `json:\"environment,omitempty\"`\n    Command          []string                        `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n    Args             []string                        `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n    Resources        corev1.ResourceRequirements     `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Shared Types:**\n```go\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    PathPrefix string       `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n    Name       string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    Port       uint32       `json:\"port\"`\n    Protocol   ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"` // Default HTTP, enum: HTTP|HTTPS\n}\n\ntype AuthModeType string  // \"picod\" | \"none\"\ntype ProtocolType string  // \"HTTP\" | \"HTTPS\"\n```\n\n### 5. Existing Workload Manager Interfaces and Patterns\n\n**Server struct:**\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config            *Config\n    router            *gin.Engine\n    httpServer        *http.Server\n    k8sClient         *K8sClient\n    sandboxController *SandboxReconciler\n    tokenCache        *TokenCache\n    informers         *Informers\n    storeClient       store.Store\n    wg                sync.WaitGroup\n}\n```\n\n**HTTP Routes:**\n| Method | Path | Auth | Handler |\n|--------|------|------|---------|\n| GET | `/health` | No | `handleHealth` |\n| POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | Conditional | `handleAgentRuntimeCreate` |\n| DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | Conditional | `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n| POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | Conditional | `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n| DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | Conditional | `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n\n**Store Interface** (`pkg/store`):\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n**K8sClient:**\n```go\ntype K8sClient struct {\n    clientset       *kubernetes.Clientset\n    dynamicClient   dynamic.Interface\n    scheme          *runtime.Scheme\n    baseConfig      *rest.Config\n    clientCache     *ClientCache\n    dynamicInformer dynamicinformer.DynamicSharedInformerFactory\n    informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n    podInformer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    podLister       listersv1.PodLister\n}\n```\n\n**SandboxInfo** (common types):\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n    SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Sandbox Controller / Processor\n\n**SandboxReconciler** (controller-runtime based):\n```go\ntype SandboxReconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme   *runtime.Scheme\n    watchers map[types.NamespacedName]chan SandboxStatusUpdate\n    mu       sync.RWMutex\n}\n\ntype SandboxStatusUpdate struct {\n    Sandbox *sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox\n}\n```\n\n- `Reconcile()`: When sandbox status becomes \"running\", notifies waiter channel (buffer 1), non-blocking send\n- `getSandboxStatus()`: Returns \"running\" if `SandboxConditionReady` is `ConditionTrue`, else \"unknown\"\n\n**Garbage Collector:**\n```go\ntype garbageCollector struct {\n    k8sClient   *K8sClient\n    interval    time.Duration   // 15 seconds\n    storeClient store.Store\n}\n```\n- Tick interval: 15s\n- Per-tick context timeout: 2 minutes\n- Batch size for listing: 16\n- Inactive cutoff: `now - DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout (15m)`\n- Expired cutoff: `now`\n\n**Agentd Reconciler** (idle cleanup, separate binary):\n```go\ntype Reconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n}\n```\n- Watches `Sandbox` resources\n- Reads `last-activity-time` annotation\n- Deletes sandbox if idle > `SessionExpirationTimeout (15m)`\n- Requeues with `time.Until(expirationTime)`\n\n### 7. Testing Patterns\n\n**Go Testing (from specs):**\n- Standard `go test -v ./...` pattern\n- Coverage: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n- E2E tests: `go test -v ./test/e2e/...` with env vars `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN`\n- Mock Kubernetes client for unit tests\n- Table-driven tests expected (standard Go pattern)\n\n**Python Testing:**\n- pytest for SDK: `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n- unittest for E2E: `test_codeinterpreter.py` with `unittest.main()`\n- Test dependencies: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`\n\n**Test Requirements (from TDD Manifest):**\n- Test-to-code ratio must be > 0.4 (40 lines of test per 100 lines of code)\n- Every source file must have a corresponding test file\n- Specific test cases defined:\n  - **WM-001**: Sandbox creation with valid AgentRuntime -> 200 OK + sessionId\n  - **WM-002**: Idempotency - same name returns same sessionId\n  - **WM-003**: Missing podTemplate -> 400 Bad Request\n  - **RT-001**: Missing Bearer Token -> 401 Unauthorized\n  - **RT-002**: Session routing with Redis mock\n  - **RT-003**: Expired session -> 404\n  - **ST-001**: Redis Set/Get of SessionInfo\n  - **ST-002**: Key TTL validation (default 24h)\n  - **PD-001**: Python code execution `print(\"hello\")` -> stdout \"hello\\n\", exitCode 0\n  - **PD-002**: Syntax error -> stderr contains \"SyntaxError\"\n  - **SDK-001**: Context manager auto-calls close()\n  - **SDK-002**: Server 500 -> custom AgentCubeError\n\n**E2E Test Infrastructure:**\n- Kind cluster named `agentcube-e2e`\n- Helm chart deployment with Redis\n- Port-forward for workloadmanager (8080) and router (8081)\n- ServiceAccount `e2e-test` with token auth\n- Fixtures: `echo_agent.yaml`, `e2e_code_interpreter.yaml`, `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### Key Project Context\n\nThis is a **benchmark/evaluation project** (SDD-TEE: Specification-Driven Development Token Efficiency Evaluation) that uses reverse-engineered specifications from the real `github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube` project. The actual Go source code does not exist locally -- only the specification documents in `specs/` describe the expected code. The benchmark's purpose is to measure token efficiency when different AI coding tools (Cursor, Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode CLI) rebuild the agentcube project using these specs via the OpenSpec (OPSX) toolchain.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2891d4b55ffeHdm59YKOImpRhq","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775816062119,"end":1775816187973}}}}
