{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775816191027,"sessionID":"ses_2891d7ce7ffeWrz5twmBqnJUqZ","part":{"id":"prt_d76e4aa5e0012F9LqyCulFUKQa","messageID":"msg_d76e4a089001L924qbfVO6F1sy","sessionID":"ses_2891d7ce7ffeWrz5twmBqnJUqZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_42385ac63fbe4e02984b3a3a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox Orchestration — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module and dependencies\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|--------|\n7: | Go module | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n8: | Go version (go.mod) | `1.24.4` |\n9: | Toolchain | `go1.24.9` |\n10: \n11: **Direct `require` (from go.mod):**  \n12: `github.com/agiledragon/gomonkey/v2 v2.13.0`, `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 v2.35.0`, `github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0`, `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.2`, `github.com/google/uuid v1.6.0`, `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.17.1`, `github.com/stretchr/testify v1.11.1`, `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.69`, `golang.org/x/net v0.47.0`, `k8s.io/api v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1`, `k8s.io/utils v0.0.0-20251002143259-bc988d571ff4`, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox v0.1.1`, `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.22.2`\n13: \n14: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n15: \n16: ### groupversion_info.go — package and scheme\n17: \n18: ```go\n19: // +groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n20: package v1alpha1\n21: \n22: var (\n23:     GroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n24:     SchemeBuilder = &scheme.Builder{GroupVersion: GroupVersion}\n25:     AddToScheme = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n26: )\n27: ```\n28: \n29: ### register.go — kind metadata\n30: \n31: ```go\n32: var (\n33:     CodeInterpreterKind             = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n34:     CodeInterpreterGroupKind        = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n35:     CodeInterpreterListKind         = \"CodeInterpreterList\"\n36:     CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n37: )\n38: \n39: var (\n40:     AgentRuntimeKind             = \"AgentRuntime\"\n41:     AgentRuntimeListKind         = \"AgentRuntimeList\"\n42:     AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n43: )\n44: \n45: var SchemeGroupVersion = GroupVersion\n46: \n47: func Resource(resource string) schema.GroupVersionResource {\n48:     return GroupVersion.WithResource(resource)\n49: }\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ### agent_type.go — AgentRuntime types\n53: \n54: ```go\n55: // +genclient\n56: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n57: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n58: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n59: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n60: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n61: type AgentRuntime struct {\n62:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n63:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n64:     Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n65:     Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n66: }\n67: \n68: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n69:     Ports []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n70:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n71:     Template *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=podTemplate\"`\n72:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n73:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n74:     SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=sessionTimeout\"`\n75:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n76:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n77:     MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=maxSessionDuration\"`\n78: }\n79: \n80: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n81:     // +optional\n82:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n83: }\n84: \n85: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n86:     // +optional\n87:     Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,rep,name=labels\"`\n88:     // +optional\n89:     Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,rep,name=annotations\"`\n90:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n91:     Spec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=spec\"`\n92: }\n93: \n94: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n95: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n96: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n97:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n98:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n99:     Items           []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### codeinterpreter_types.go — CodeInterpreter and shared types\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: // +genclient\n107: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n108: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n109: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n110: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n111: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n112: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n113:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n114:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n115:     Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n116:     Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n117: }\n118: \n119: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n120:     // +optional\n121:     Ports []TargetPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n122:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n123:     Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate `json:\"template\"`\n124:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n125:     SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n126:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n127:     MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n128:     // +optional\n129:     WarmPoolSize *int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n130:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"picod\"\n131:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n132:     // +optional\n133:     AuthMode AuthModeType `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`\n134: }\n135: \n136: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n137:     // +optional\n138:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n139:     // +optional\n140:     Ready bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n141: }\n142: \n143: type CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {\n144:     // +optional\n145:     Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n146:     // +optional\n147:     Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n148:     // +optional\n149:     RuntimeClassName *string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n150:     Image string `json:\"image,omitempty\"`\n151:     // +optional\n152:     ImagePullPolicy corev1.PullPolicy `json:\"imagePullPolicy,omitempty\"`\n153:     // +optional\n154:     // +patchMergeKey=name\n155:     // +patchStrategy=merge\n156:     // +listType=map\n157:     // +listMapKey=name\n158:     ImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference `json:\"imagePullSecrets,omitempty\"`\n159:     // +optional\n160:     Environment []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"environment,omitempty\"`\n161:     // +optional\n162:     // +listType=atomic\n163:     Command []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n164:     // +optional\n165:     Args []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n166:     // +optional\n167:     Resources corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n168: }\n169: \n170: type TargetPort struct {\n171:     // +optional\n172:     PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n173:     // +optional\n174:     Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n175:     Port uint32 `json:\"port\"`\n176:     // +kubebuilder:default=HTTP\n177:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS;\n178:     Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n179: }\n180: \n181: type AuthModeType string\n182: \n183: const (\n184:     AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n185:     AuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n186: )\n187: \n188: type ProtocolType string\n189: \n190: const (\n191:     ProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n192:     ProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n193: )\n194: \n195: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n196: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n197: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n198:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n199:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n200:     Items           []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n201: }\n202: ```\n203: \n204: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n205: \n206: ```go\n207: const (\n208:     AgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n209:     CodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n210:     SandboxKind         = \"Sandbox\"\n211:     SandboxClaimsKind   = \"SandboxClaim\"\n212: )\n213: \n214: type SandboxInfo struct {\n215:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n216:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n217:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n218:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n219:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n220:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n221:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n222:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n223:     Status string `json:\"status\"`\n224: }\n225: \n226: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n227:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n228:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n229:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n230: }\n231: \n232: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n233:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n234:     Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n235:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n236: }\n237: \n238: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n239:     SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n240:     SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n241:     SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n242:     EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n243: }\n244: \n245: func (car *CreateSandboxRequest) Validate() error\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/api`\n249: \n250: ```go\n251: const (\n252:     resourceGroup               = \"agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n253:     sessionResourceName         = \"sessions\"\n254:     agentRuntimeResourceName    = \"agentruntimes\"\n255:     codeInterpreterResourceName = \"codeinterpreters\"\n256: )\n257: \n258: var (\n259:     ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound    = errors.New(\"agent runtime not found\")\n260:     ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound = errors.New(\"code interpreter not found\")\n261:     ErrTemplateMissing         = errors.New(\"resource has no pod template\")\n262:     ErrPublicKeyMissing        = errors.New(\"public key not yet loaded from Router Secret\")\n263: )\n264: \n265: func NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID string) error\n266: func NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(namespace, name, kind string) error\n267: func NewUpstreamUnavailableError(err error) error\n268: func NewInternalError(err error) error\n269: ```\n270: \n271: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n272: \n273: ### Config and Server\n274: \n275: ```go\n276: type Config struct {\n277:     Port             string\n278:     RuntimeClassName string\n279:     EnableTLS        bool\n280:     TLSCert          string\n281:     TLSKey           string\n282:     EnableAuth       bool\n283: }\n284: \n285: type Server struct {\n286:     config            *Config\n287:     router            *gin.Engine\n288:     httpServer        *http.Server\n289:     k8sClient         *K8sClient\n290:     sandboxController *SandboxReconciler\n291:     tokenCache        *TokenCache\n292:     informers         *Informers\n293:     storeClient       store.Store\n294:     wg                sync.WaitGroup\n295: }\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### HTTP routes\n299: \n300: | Method | Path | Auth middleware | Handler |\n301: |--------|------|-----------------|---------|\n302: | GET | `/health` | No | `handleHealth` |\n303: | POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | If `EnableAuth` | `handleAgentRuntimeCreate` |\n304: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | If `EnableAuth` | `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n305: | POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | If `EnableAuth` | `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n306: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | If `EnableAuth` | `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n307: \n308: ### ErrorResponse\n309: \n310: ```go\n311: type ErrorResponse struct {\n312:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n313: }\n314: ```\n315: \n316: ### K8sClient and defaults\n317: \n318: ```go\n319: const (\n320:     DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n321:     DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n322: )\n323: \n324: var (\n325:     SessionIdLabelKey         = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n326:     WorkloadNameLabelKey      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n327:     SandboxNameLabelKey       = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n328:     LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"\n329:     IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n330: )\n331: \n332: type K8sClient struct {\n333:     clientset       *kubernetes.Clientset\n334:     dynamicClient   dynamic.Interface\n335:     scheme          *runtime.Scheme\n336:     baseConfig      *rest.Config\n337:     clientCache     *ClientCache\n338:     dynamicInformer dynamicinformer.DynamicSharedInformerFactory\n339:     informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n340:     podInformer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n341:     podLister       listersv1.PodLister\n342: }\n343: ```\n344: \n345: - REST config: `QPS = 50`, `Burst = 100`; in-cluster config else kubeconfig loading rules.\n346: - `NewClientCache(100)` for user dynamic clients.\n347: \n348: ### GVR variables (`informers.go`)\n349: \n350: ```go\n351: var (\n352:     AgentRuntimeGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n353:         Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\",\n354:     }\n355:     CodeInterpreterGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n356:         Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\",\n357:     }\n358:     SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n359:         Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n360:     }\n361:     SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n362:         Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n363:     }\n364: )\n365: ```\n366: \n367: ### Identity secret (workload_builder.go)\n368: \n369: ```go\n370: const (\n371:     IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n372:     PublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"\n373: )\n374: \n375: var IdentitySecretNamespace = \"default\" // overridden by env AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE if set\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### Sandbox reconciler\n379: \n380: ```go\n381: type SandboxReconciler struct {\n382:     client.Client\n383:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n384:     watchers map[types.NamespacedName]chan SandboxStatusUpdate\n385:     mu       sync.RWMutex\n386: }\n387: \n388: type SandboxStatusUpdate struct {\n389:     Sandbox *sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox\n390: }\n391: ```\n392: \n393: - `Reconcile`: when `getSandboxStatus(sandbox) == \"running\"`, notify waiter channel (buffer 1), non-blocking send with `default` branch warning on full channel.\n394: - `getSandboxStatus`: returns `\"running\"` if a condition has `Type == string(sandboxv1alpha1.SandboxConditionReady)` and `Status == metav1.ConditionTrue`, else `\"unknown\"`.\n395: \n396: ### Garbage collector\n397: \n398: ```go\n399: const gcOnceTimeout = 2 * time.Minute\n400: \n401: type garbageCollector struct {\n402:     k8sClient   *K8sClient\n403:     interval    time.Duration\n404:     storeClient store.Store\n405: }\n406: ```\n407: \n408: - `newGarbageCollector(k8s, store, 15*time.Second)` — **GC interval: 15s**.\n409: - Per tick: `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout), 16)` — **batch size 16**.\n410: - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, time.Now(), 16)` — **batch size 16**.\n411: - Single tick context timeout: **2 minutes**.\n412: \n413: ### Token cache\n414: \n415: - `NewTokenCache(1000, 5*time.Minute)` — max entries **1000**, TTL **5m** per entry (LRU + last-access expiry).\n416: \n417: ### Auth context keys\n418: \n419: ```go\n420: type contextKey string\n421: \n422: const (\n423:     contextKeyUserToken          contextKey = \"userToken\"\n424:     contextKeyServiceAccount     contextKey = \"serviceAccount\"\n425:     contextKeyServiceAccountName contextKey = \"serviceAccountName\"\n426:     contextKeyNamespace          contextKey = \"namespace\"\n427: )\n428: ```\n429: \n430: ### CLI flags (`cmd/workload-manager/main.go`)\n431: \n432: | Flag | Default | Meaning |\n433: |------|---------|---------|\n434: | `-port` | `8080` | API port |\n435: | `-runtime-class-name` | `kuasar-vmm` | Stored on `Config.RuntimeClassName` (flag parsed in `main`; **not read** elsewhere in `pkg/workloadmanager` in current source) |\n436: | `-enable-tls` | `false` | TLS |\n437: | `-tls-cert` | `\"\"` | Cert path |\n438: | `-tls-key` | `\"\"` | Key path |\n439: | `-enable-auth` | `false` | TokenReview auth |\n440: \n441: - Controller-runtime manager: metrics bind `0`, health probe `0`.\n442: - Shutdown: HTTP shutdown timeout **15s**, then cancel ctx, `WaitForBackgroundWorkers`, `CloseStore`.\n443: \n444: ### Store dependency\n445: \n446: ```go\n447: // github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\n448: type Store interface {\n449:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n450:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n451:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n452:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n453:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n454:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n455:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n456:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n457:     Close() error\n458: }\n459: ```\n460: \n461: Server uses `store.Storage()` singleton.\n462: \n463: ### Sandbox build notes\n464: \n465: - AgentRuntime: sandbox name `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`, UUID session ID, ports from `spec.Ports`, TTL/idle from `MaxSessionDuration` / `SessionTimeout` when non-nil.\n466: - CodeInterpreter: default ports if empty: single `TargetPort{Port:8080, Protocol:ProtocolTypeHTTP, PathPrefix:\"/\"}`; if `WarmPoolSize > 0`: creates `SandboxClaim` + minimal `Sandbox` metadata only, `sandboxEntry.Kind = SandboxClaimsKind`; else builds full `Sandbox` with container `code-interpreter` and optional `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode == picod`.\n467: - `buildSandboxObject`: APIVersion `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, Kind `Sandbox`, labels include `managed-by: agentcube-workload-manager`, annotation `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey` = idle duration string, lifecycle `ShutdownTime` = now+TTL, `Replicas: ptr.To[int32](1)`.\n468: \n469: ### Pod name annotation\n470: \n471: - Read from created sandbox: key from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/controllers`.`SandboxPodNameAnnotation` (comment in source documents value `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`).\n472: \n473: ## CodeInterpreter controller (supplementary)\n474: \n475: - Reconciles `CodeInterpreter`; when `WarmPoolSize > 0` ensures `SandboxTemplate` (name = CI name) and `SandboxWarmPool` (name = CI name, replicas = WarmPoolSize, templateRef name = CI name); injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` in template unless `AuthModeNone`; requeues 5s if public key not cached and auth not none.\n\n(End of file - total 475 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox Orchestration — Design\n\n## Module and dependencies\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|--------|\n| Go module | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Go version (go.mod) | `1.24.4` |\n| Toolchain | `go1.24.9` |\n\n**Direct `require` (from go.mod):**  \n`github.com/agiledragon/gomonkey/v2 v2.13.0`, `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 v2.35.0`, `github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0`, `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.2`, `github.com/google/uuid v1.6.0`, `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.17.1`, `github.com/stretchr/testify v1.11.1`, `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.69`, `golang.org/x/net v0.47.0`, `k8s.io/api v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1`, `k8s.io/utils v0.0.0-20251002143259-bc988d571ff4`, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox v0.1.1`, `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.22.2`\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n### groupversion_info.go — package and scheme\n\n```go\n// +groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\npackage v1alpha1","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/sandbox-orchestration/design.md","time":{"start":1775816191019,"end":1775816191026}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775816191672,"sessionID":"ses_2891d7ce7ffeWrz5twmBqnJUqZ","part":{"id":"prt_d76e4ad03001QtCTM1s4N3oymr","messageID":"msg_d76e4a089001L924qbfVO6F1sy","sessionID":"ses_2891d7ce7ffeWrz5twmBqnJUqZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_f866fbf415c94f4aa82fe76b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775816191665,"end":1775816191670}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775816192376,"sessionID":"ses_2891d7ce7ffeWrz5twmBqnJUqZ","part":{"id":"prt_d76e4af41001dwGIOY8nypS2EW","messageID":"msg_d76e4a089001L924qbfVO6F1sy","sessionID":"ses_2891d7ce7ffeWrz5twmBqnJUqZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3d1cecd8a2b34e32a2eaa007","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Orchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\n9: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n13: - **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n14: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\n17: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n20: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`\n21: - **WHEN** the template is deserialized\n22: - **THEN** `labels` and `annotations` are optional maps and `spec` is required and of type `corev1.PodSpec`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime status\n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with optional `conditions` of type `[]metav1.Condition`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Conditions optional\n28: - **GIVEN** a minimal `AgentRuntime` object\n29: - **WHEN** status is omitted or empty\n30: - **THEN** deserialization succeeds without requiring `conditions`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD schema\n33: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the same API group/version with subresource `status` and print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter GVR\n36: - **GIVEN** dynamic client configuration for workload templates\n37: - **WHEN** GVR is constructed for `codeinterpreters`\n38: - **THEN** group is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, resource `codeinterpreters`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with: optional `Ports` (`[]TargetPort`, JSON `ports`); required `Template` (`*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, JSON `template`); optional `SessionTimeout` with default `\"15m\"`; optional `MaxSessionDuration` with default `\"8h\"`; optional `WarmPoolSize` (`*int32`); optional `AuthMode` (`AuthModeType`, JSON `authMode`) with default `\"picod\"` and enum `picod` or `none`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Auth mode constants\n44: - **GIVEN** API constants for auth mode\n45: - **WHEN** `AuthMode` is compared\n46: - **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` equals `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` equals `\"none\"`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n49: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with optional `conditions` and optional boolean `ready`.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Ready flag\n52: - **GIVEN** a reconciled `CodeInterpreter`\n53: - **WHEN** status is updated by the controller\n54: - **THEN** `status.ready` may be set to `true` alongside a `Ready` condition\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: TargetPort and Protocol types\n57: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` with optional `pathPrefix`, optional `name`, required `port` (`uint32`), and required `protocol` (`ProtocolType`) with kubebuilder default `HTTP` and enum `HTTP` or `HTTPS`.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Protocol constants\n60: - **GIVEN** port configuration without explicit protocol in some code paths\n61: - **WHEN** defaults apply at API level\n62: - **THEN** default protocol is `HTTP` per kubebuilder marker\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Workload manager health endpoint\n65: The system SHALL serve `GET /health` without authentication and SHALL respond `200` with JSON body `{\"status\":\"healthy\"}`.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Health bypasses auth middleware\n68: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n69: - **WHEN** a client calls `GET /health` with no `Authorization` header\n70: - **THEN** the response status is 200 and body contains `\"status\":\"healthy\"`\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Workload manager v1 routes and middleware\n73: The system SHALL mount a `/v1` route group with `loggingMiddleware` then `authMiddleware` (order preserved), and SHALL register `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Session id path parameter\n76: - **GIVEN** a delete request\n77: - **WHEN** Gin binds the path\n78: - **THEN** the session identifier is read from parameter name `sessionId` (camelCase)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Create sandbox request validation\n81: The system SHALL accept JSON for create endpoints matching `CreateSandboxRequest` with fields `kind`, `name`, `namespace`; SHALL overwrite `kind` from the handler (`AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter`); and SHALL reject requests where `kind` is not one of those, `namespace` is empty, or `name` is empty.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Validation failure returns 400\n84: - **GIVEN** the handler sets `sandboxReq.Kind` from the route and `Validate()` is called\n85: - **WHEN** `namespace` or `name` is empty in the JSON body\n86: - **THEN** the response is 400 and the error message includes `required` (e.g. `namespace is required` or `name is required`)\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create sandbox success response\n89: On successful creation the system SHALL respond `200` with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing `sessionId`, `sandboxId`, `sandboxName`, and `entryPoints` (each entry point has `path`, `protocol`, `endpoint`).\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Entry points reflect TargetPort and pod IP\n92: - **GIVEN** a sandbox reaches running state and pod IP is resolved\n93: - **WHEN** the response is built\n94: - **THEN** each entry point `endpoint` is `host:port` joined from pod IP and configured port, with protocol string from `TargetPort.Protocol`\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Create sandbox error responses\n97: The system SHALL return `400` with `{\"message\":...}` for invalid JSON or validation failure; `404` with message from wrapped not-found errors when AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is missing from informer cache; `401` with message from client extraction error when `EnableAuth` is true; `500` with `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}` for other create failures including timeout.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: JSON parse failure\n100: - **GIVEN** a non-JSON body to `POST /v1/agent-runtime`\n101: - **WHEN** the handler binds JSON\n102: - **THEN** status is 400 and message is `Invalid request body`\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Optional Bearer authentication via TokenReview\n105: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>` with exactly two space-separated fields; SHALL validate via `authentication/v1` `TokenReview` create; SHALL cache results in an LRU cache (capacity 1000, entry TTL 5 minutes); and SHALL store in context: token, full username, service account name, namespace parsed from `system:serviceaccount:<ns>:<name>`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Missing header\n108: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n109: - **WHEN** `/v1/...` is called without `Authorization`\n110: - **THEN** response is 401 with message `Missing authorization header` and handler chain aborts\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: TokenReview success path\n113: - **GIVEN** a valid service account token and `EnableAuth` true\n114: - **WHEN** `validateServiceAccountToken` runs with cache miss\n115: - **THEN** the server creates `TokenReview` with `spec.token` set and uses `status.user.username` when `status.authenticated` is true\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Authenticated Kubernetes operations use user client\n118: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL use a per-user dynamic client (from bearer token) for creating/deleting `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` resources; when false, SHALL use the manager’s in-cluster/default dynamic client.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: User client cache key\n121: - **GIVEN** repeated requests from the same namespace and service account name\n122: - **WHEN** `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient` is used\n123: - **THEN** the cache key is `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation ordering and store placeholder\n126: The system SHALL call `StoreSandbox` with a placeholder `SandboxInfo` before creating the `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` in the API; SHALL register a one-shot watcher before create; SHALL wait up to 2 minutes for sandbox status `running` from the reconciler; SHALL resolve pod IP and then `UpdateSandbox` with full info; and SHALL roll back the created CR on failure after the wait (delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim within a 30s timeout context).\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Watcher registration before create\n129: - **GIVEN** a create request reaches `createSandbox`\n130: - **WHEN** the Sandbox CR is created\n131: - **THEN** `WatchSandboxOnce` was already invoked for that namespace/name\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Timeout returns error\n134: - **GIVEN** no running notification within 2 minutes\n135: - **WHEN** the select completes\n136: - **THEN** creation fails with error `sandbox creation timed out` and HTTP 500 is returned to the client\n137: \n138: ### Requirement: Pod IP resolution\n139: The system SHALL prefer pod name equal to sandbox name; if annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` exists on the created Sandbox (from agent-sandbox controller), SHALL use that as pod name; SHALL load pod from informer cache and require `PodRunning` and non-empty `PodIP`; otherwise SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>` and pick the pod whose controller owner reference is kind `Sandbox` and name matches.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Pod not running yields error\n142: - **GIVEN** a matching pod in non-Running phase\n143: - **WHEN** IP is resolved\n144: - **THEN** resolution fails with an error indicating the pod is not running\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: Delete sandbox by session\n147: The system SHALL load session from store by `sessionId`; on `ErrNotFound` return `404` with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`; delete `SandboxClaim` when stored `Kind` is `SandboxClaim`, else delete `Sandbox`; treat API `NotFound` on delete as success; then `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`; success response `200` `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`.\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Store miss\n150: - **GIVEN** no session key in store\n151: - **WHEN** DELETE is invoked\n152: - **THEN** HTTP status is 404 and message mentions the session id\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: Garbage collection loop\n155: The system SHALL run a background goroutine tick every 15 seconds; each tick SHALL use a context timeout of 2 minutes; SHALL query inactive sessions with cutoff `now - 15m` and batch limit 16; SHALL query expired sessions with `before = now` and batch limit 16; SHALL merge lists and delete each unique workload then remove store entry by session ID.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: GC uses DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout\n158: - **GIVEN** GC lists inactive sandboxes\n159: - **WHEN** computing the inactive cutoff\n160: - **THEN** `inactiveTime` equals `time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)` where `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` is 15 minutes\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: HTTP server and process behavior\n163: The system SHALL use Gin with `gin.New()` for the workload API; SHALL serve with `h2c` wrapping and `http2.Server`; SHALL use `ReadTimeout` 15s and `IdleTimeout` 90s for HTTP when not using TLS; SHALL ping the store before listening; SHALL sync informers (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod) with up to 1 minute wait; on SIGINT/SIGTERM SHALL shutdown HTTP within 15s, cancel context, wait for background workers, then `Close()` the store.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: TLS requires cert and key\n166: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` is true and cert or key path is empty\n167: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n168: - **THEN** it returns an error that TLS is enabled but cert/key not provided\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: API error helper constants\n171: The system SHALL define in package `api` the sentinel errors `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound`, `ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound`, `ErrTemplateMissing`, `ErrPublicKeyMissing`, and SHALL map `CodeInterpreter` kind to group-resource `agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters` and default kinds to `agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes` for `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError`.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Session not found uses API machinery\n174: - **GIVEN** `NewSessionNotFoundError(\"sid\")`\n175: - **WHEN** the error is inspected as `APIStatus`\n176: - **THEN** the group resource is `agentcube.volcano.sh, Resource=sessions` and name is the session id\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n\n## Purpose\nOrchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\nThe system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n\n#### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n- **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n- **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md","time":{"start":1775816192369,"end":1775816192374}}}}
